OL,3,CControversial commissioner who led
OL,4,C#300m of council cuts to step down
OL,6,FMr Caller had blocked an attempt by
OL,7,Fcouncillors to scrutinise the
OL,8,Fcontroversial decision.
OL,10,FThe closures were part of a wider
OL,11,Feffort to address a #1.95 million
OL,12,Fbudget gap for 2024`25 and #3.35
OL,13,Fmillion in 2025`26.
OL,15,FFollowing the cabinet's decision to
OL,16,Fclose the centres, six councillors
OL,17,Fsought to have it reviewed by a
OL,18,Fscrutiny committee through the formal
OL,19,F"call-in" process. But Max Caller
OL,20,Foverruled them, blocking further
OL,21,Fexamination by the scrutiny committee.
